# lodor#7 disc-1-first, LOCAL-ONLY .m3u: the playlist lists only present discs, so the
# hook detects the incomplete set via `lodor-sync --check-rom` (manifest census), NOT
# by scanning the playlist. complete=0 -> --fetch-next-disc fires, the disc lands, the
# post-fetch --check-rom reads complete, and the launch proceeds (exit 0). The card
# here carries the legacy full-list shape (stub disc 2 listed) — detection must not care.
desc fetch hook (lodor#7): --check-rom says incomplete -> --fetch-next-disc lands disc 2
invoke prehook
config paired
romarg Roms/PlayStation (PS)/✓ FF7.m3u
sdtext Roms/PlayStation (PS)/✓ FF7.m3u	FF7/D1.chd\nFF7/D2.chd\n
sdfile+ Roms/PlayStation (PS)/FF7/D1.chd
sdfile Roms/PlayStation (PS)/FF7/D2.chd
engine 0|RESULT complete=0 discs_total=2 discs_present=1
engine 0|RESULT fetched=1 complete=1 discs_total=2 discs_present=2
engine 0|RESULT complete=1 discs_total=2 discs_present=2
engine 0|
expect_exit 0
expect_trace ENGINE --check-rom
expect_trace ENGINE --fetch-next-disc
expect_file_has Roms/PlayStation (PS)/FF7/D2.chd	DISCBYTES
